<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1931-08-24T04:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1931-08-24T04:00:00-05:00" n="198" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d198">
                                <note rend="inline" type="source">462.00R296/5001: Telegram</note>
                                <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Yugoslavia</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Prince</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                                            State</gloss></hi></head>
                                <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Belgrade</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-08-24T10:00:00+01:00">August 24, 1931—10 a.m.</date><lb/>[Received 10:20
                                        a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                                <p>40. Yugoslav Government disturbed over semi-official news from
                                    Washington to effect Hoover Plan will be applied Yugoslavia
                                    despite non-acceptance. Finance Ministry operating radical
                                    budget cuts every Ministry but states cannot possibly meet
                                    Hoover requirements in addition present abnormal burdens
                                    incident to recent currency stabilization and deficit incurred
                                    through aid guaranteed grain <pb facs="0350" n="236" xml:id="pg_236"/> farmers. Finance Minister expresses
                                    belief, hope Yugoslavia will receive aid this crisis essential
                                    to preservation currency and credit.</p>
                                <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Prince</hi></signed></closer>
                            </div>
                            </body></text></TEI>